If a cooperative desires to issue nonvoting shares of stock, its articles of incorporation, in addition to the provisions of subsection (1) of this section, shall state:
The total number of such shares of stock which may be issued and the par value of each share;
The fixed or maximum rate of dividends on the par value of such shares of stock, in either case not exceeding four percent (4%) per annum, and whether dividends shall be cumulative or noncumulative;
Whether such shares of stock may be issued to members only or to members and nonmembers;
The maximum number of such shares of stock which may be owned by any person;
The terms and conditions on which such shares of stock may be transferred, redeemed or retired.
